{{#>base}}
{{#*inline 'content'}}

<div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
  <h1 style="font-size:2rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color: #e94560;">
    Competition Instructions
  </h1>
  <p style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Read carefully before you begin.</p>

  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #e94560;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1rem; font-size:1.1rem;">Duration</h2>
    <p>This competition lasts <strong>1 hour and 15 minutes</strong>. The timer will start at the time announced by the organizer — check the countdown bar above. Manage your time wisely.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #0f9b8e;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1rem; font-size:1.1rem;">Questions</h2>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.2rem; line-height:2;">
      <li>There are <strong>2 questions</strong> available. You are expected to answer <strong>at least one</strong>.</li>
      <li>You may attempt both questions for a higher score.</li>
      <li>Click on a question title to see the full problem statement.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #2196f3;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1rem; font-size:1.1rem;">Allowed Languages</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">You may write your solution in any of the following languages:</p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:0.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <span class="badge badge-info" style="font-size:0.9rem; padding:4px 16px;">Python</span>
      <span class="badge badge-info" style="font-size:0.9rem; padding:4px 16px;">JavaScript</span>
      <span class="badge badge-info" style="font-size:0.9rem; padding:4px 16px;">C</span>
      <span class="badge badge-info" style="font-size:0.9rem; padding:4px 16px;">Java</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #ff9800;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1rem; font-size:1.1rem;">Submitting Your Code</h2>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.2rem; line-height:2;">
      <li>You can <strong>paste your code</strong> directly into the editor on the question page.</li>
      <li>Alternatively, you can <strong>upload your code file</strong> (.py, .js, .c, .java).</li>
      <li>Select the correct programming language before submitting.</li>
      <li>You may submit <strong>multiple times</strong>. Each submission is tested and you will see the result immediately.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:2rem; border-left: 4px solid #9c27b0;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1rem; font-size:1.1rem;">Rules</h2>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.2rem; line-height:2;">
      <li>You are <strong>NOT allowed</strong> to access the internet during this competition.</li>
      <li>All solutions are tested automatically against hidden test cases.</li>
      <li>A result of <strong style="color:#4caf50;">ACCEPTED</strong> means all test cases passed.</li>
      <li>A result of <strong style="color:#f44336;">WRONG ANSWER</strong> means your output doesn't match expected output.</li>
      <li>A result of <strong style="color:#f44336;">COMPILE ERROR</strong> or <strong style="color:#f44336;">RUNTIME ERROR</strong> means your code has a bug.</li>
      <li>Academic honesty is expected. Do your own work.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div style="text-align:center;">
    <a href="/questions" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size:1.1rem; padding:0.75rem 2.5rem;">
      View Problems &rarr;
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

{{/inline}}
{{/base}}